Create a String from a Character Array in Java using StringBuffer

You are working on a Java program that requires creating a string from a 
character array. In this scenario, you are allowed to use a StringBuffer to 
achieve this task.

Write a Java program that takes a character array as input and creates a 
string from the characters in the array using a StringBuffer.

Test Case : 1
Expected output :
Created string: H e l l o
Actual output :
Created string: H e l l o

Test Case : 2
Expected output :
Created string: J a v a
Actual output :
Created string: J a v a
